<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB06190</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PROVIDING FOR THE PROTECTION OF EMPLOYEES IN THE BUSINESS PROCESS OUTSOURCING (BPO) INDUSTRY</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Aims to maintain a balance between the protection of the interests and welfare of the workers and employees in the B P O industry and to ensure that the impact of its growth be trickled down to most of the populations.

Enumerates several rights of B P O employees as regards to organizing/joining labor organizations; safe and
healthy working environment; an hour meal break; respect for privacy when it comes to personal phone calls, in compliance with the Data Privacy Act; comfortable resting area for night shift employees until daybreak;
and to be informed of the terms and conditions of their contract.    

</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>CASTELO, PRECIOUS HIPOLITO</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2020-02-05</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Del Mar (000 2020-02-12)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON LABOR AND EMPLOYMENT ON 2020-02-10</td></tr></table>